# Spectrum 2 UI only

Deckhand’s React UI uses **Adobe React Spectrum 2** (`@react-spectrum/s2`).

## Required

- Components and icons from `@react-spectrum/s2` and `@react-spectrum/s2/icons/*`
- Layout/tokens via `import { style, iconStyle } from '@react-spectrum/s2/style' with { type: 'macro' }`
- Root: `Provider`, `@react-spectrum/s2/page.css`, `ToastContainer` / `ToastQueue`
- Button events: `onPress` (not `onClick`) on Spectrum components
- `style()` arguments must be **static** object literals (build-time macro)

## Do not add

- Radix UI, shadcn/ui, Tailwind utility styling, MUI, Chakra, Ant Design, or parallel component kits
- Lucide / other icon sets when an S2 icon exists
- Sonner or non-Spectrum toast libraries

## App helpers

Small Spectrum helpers live under `app/src/components/spectrum/` (`Tip`, `StatusBadge`, `RowMenu`, `Field`/`Area`). Prefer these or raw `@react-spectrum/s2` — do not recreate `components/ui` or shadcn-style wrappers.

## Custom widgets

When S2 has no component (e.g. xterm, custom charts), style chrome with Spectrum tokens / `style` macros (and React Aria if needed). Do not reintroduce a second design system.
